These are names of financial-media, investing-newsletter, stock-research/tool, market-data, or adjacent investor-information publishers.

Merge obvious variants of the same publisher or consumer-facing brand:
- spelling, punctuation, capitalization, legal-suffix, and domain variants;
- "The" prefix variants, e.g. "The Motley Fool" and "Motley Fool";
- same publisher with ".com", "Media", "Newsletter", or similar descriptive suffixes when the public-facing entity is clearly the same.

Do NOT merge distinct brands within the same corporate family unless the names clearly refer to the same publisher surface. Parent companies, segments, and brands can each be legitimate distinct publisher entities when the cited artifact uses that level of attribution.
